Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy applies to the Never Have I Ever: Party Game mobile application (hereinafter referred to as the "Application"), developed by Argpromt (hereinafter referred to as the "Service Provider"). The Application is provided as a free service, intended for use "AS IS".

Information Collection and Use

The Application may collect certain information automatically when you download and use it. This data may include:
- Your device’s Internet Protocol (IP) address
- The pages or screens you visit and the time and date of those visits
- The amount of time spent within the Application
- Your mobile operating system

The Application does not collect precise location data from your device.

In some cases, the Service Provider may ask you to provide personally identifiable information to enhance your experience. Any such data will be used solely as described in this policy and retained securely.

Third-Party Services

The Application may share aggregated, anonymized data with third-party services to help improve performance and user experience.

The Application integrates third-party services that may collect data according to their own privacy policies. You can review them here:
- Google Play Services: https://policies.google.com/privacy
- Unity Ads: https://unity.com/legal/privacy-policy

The Service Provider may disclose user-provided and automatically collected information:
- If required by law (e.g., in response to a subpoena or court order)
- To protect user rights, personal safety, prevent fraud, or respond to a government request
- To trusted service providers working on their behalf, who have agreed to process such data in compliance with this policy

Opt-Out Rights

You can stop all information collection by uninstalling the Application. Use the standard uninstall process on your mobile device or through the app store.

Data Retention

The Service Provider will retain user-provided data as long as the Application is in use and for a reasonable period afterward.
To request deletion of your data, contact: argpromt@gmail.com

Children’s Privacy

The Application is not intended for children under the age of 13. The Service Provider does not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

If it is discovered that such information has been provided by a child, it will be promptly deleted.
If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided personal data, please contact argpromt@gmail.com immediately.

Security

The Service Provider is committed to protecting your information. Reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards are implemented to protect your data from unauthorized access or disclosure.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with the updated effective date. Continued use of the Application indicates acceptance of the revised policy.

Effective Date: June 19, 2025

Your Consent

By using the Application, you agree to the collection and use of your information as described in this Privacy Policy.

Contact Us

If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact:
argpromt@gmail.com
